</table><para id="import-auto-id1172507233054">The value of <emphasis effect="italics">d</emphasis> for each of these planes can be calculated using <link target-id="eip-96"/>, where <emphasis effect="italics">a</emphasis> is the lattice parameter of the crystal.</para><note id="eip-989">The lattice constant, or lattice parameter, refers to the constant distance between unit cells in a crystal lattice. </note><equation id="eip-96"><m:math>
<m:apply><m:eq/><m:apply><m:divide/><m:cn>1</m:cn><m:apply><m:power/><m:ci>d</m:ci><m:cn>2</m:cn></m:apply></m:apply><m:apply><m:divide/><m:apply><m:plus/><m:apply><m:power/><m:ci>h</m:ci><m:cn>2</m:cn></m:apply><m:apply><m:power/><m:ci>k</m:ci><m:cn>2</m:cn></m:apply><m:apply><m:power/><m:ci>l</m:ci><m:cn>2</m:cn></m:apply></m:apply><m:apply><m:power/><m:ci>a</m:ci><m:cn>2</m:cn></m:apply></m:apply></m:apply>
</m:math></equation><example id="eip-962">

