        <para id="import-auto-id1172481923763">Calculate the lattice parameter using <link target-id="eip-96"/>,</para>
        <para id="import-auto-id1172472403824">1/2.3624<sup>2 </sup>= (1<sup>2</sup>+ 1<sup>2</sup>+ l<sup>2</sup>)/<emphasis effect="italics">a</emphasis><sup>2</sup></para><para id="import-auto-id1172478660108"><emphasis effect="italics">a</emphasis> = 4.0918 Å</para><para id="eip-800">The last column gives a list of integers, which corresponds to the <emphasis effect="italics">h</emphasis><sup>2</sup>+<emphasis effect="italics">k</emphasis><sup>2</sup>+<emphasis effect="italics">l</emphasis><sup>2</sup> values of the FCC lattice diffraction. Hence, the Ag nanoparticles have a FCC structure.</para>

